com.sap.conn.idoc

Interface IDocDocumentList

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable

    public interface IDocDocumentList
extends Serializable
    Interface that serves as a container for storing and managing a list of documents of the same kind (also known as IDoc package).

      • add

        boolean add(IDocDocument document)
     throws IDocIllegalTypeException
        Adds a document to this list.
        Parameters:
        document - the document object to add.
        Returns:
        always true (as per the general contract of JDK 1.2 java.util.Collection interface).
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if document is null.
        IDocIllegalTypeException - if the document object is not compatible with this document list.
        See Also:
        isCompatible(IDocDocument)

      • indexOf

        int indexOf(IDocDocument document)
        Searches for the first occurrence of the given document, testing for equality using the equals method.
        Parameters:
        document - document which the list is searched for.
        Returns:
        the index of the first occurrence of the document in this list; returns -1 if the document was not found.

      • indexOf

        int indexOf(IDocDocument document,
            int startIndex)
        Searches for the first occurrence of the given document, beginning the search at the specified index and testing for equality using the equals method.
        Parameters:
        document - document which the list is searched for.
        startIndex - the index to start searching from.
        Returns:
        the index of the first occurrence of the document in this list at position startIndex or later; returns -1 if the document was not found at position startIndex or later.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - if startIndex is out of range (startIndex < 0 || (startIndex > 0 && startIndex >= size())).

      • isEmpty

        boolean isEmpty()
        Checks if this list is empty and does not contain any documents.
        Returns:
        true if this list is empty and does not contain any documents; false otherwise.

      • isCompatible

        boolean isCompatible(IDocDocument document)
        Checks if a document is compatible to this document list. If the document is compatible it can be added to this list by using the method add(IDocDocument document).
        Parameters:
        document - the document object to check
        Returns:
        true if the passed document object is compatible, false otherwise.
        Since:
        IDocLibrary 3.0.8
        See Also:
        add(IDocDocument)

      • remove

        IDocDocument remove(int index)
        Removes the document at the specified position from this list. Shifts any subsequent documents to the left (subtracts one from their indices).
        Parameters:
        index - the index of the document to be removed.
        Returns:
        the document that was removed from the list.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - if index is out of range (index < 0 || index >= size()).

      • remove

        boolean remove(IDocDocument document)
        Removes the specified document from this list testing for equality using the equals method. Shifts any subsequent documents to the left (subtracts one from their indices).
        Parameters:
        document - document to be removed from this list, if present.
        Returns:
        true if this list contained the specified document and the document was removed; false otherwise.

      • trimToSize

        void trimToSize()
        Trims the capacity of this list instance to be the list's current size. An application can use this operation to minimize the storage of this list instance.
